description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced and motivated adult speech and language therapist to join our team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is an interesting mix of working on the general medical wards and stroke unit completing assessment, treatment and advice to adults with communication and swallowing difficulties. Working alongside a supportive team, you can enjoy the fast paced environment of an acute setting where multi disciplinary team working is essential. We are a friendly and forward thinking service, with excellent systems in place for supervision, support and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the acute setting, our integrated service provides support for Community Rehabilitation, Adults with Learning Disability and Voice and Head and Neck outpatient services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are welcome to the Speech and Language Therapy Department at North Devon District Hospital on 01271 322388.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working Pattern: Monday – Friday, 8.30am - 4.30pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return to Practice applications will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 08/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
